Email requests will fail to be created if the message has an attachment (such as an image in the signature) and the reporter doesn't have the *Create attachments* permission. In this case, the whole message will be dropped and the message below will appear in the mail logs:
{panel}
Your request could not be created. Please check the fields have been correctly filled in.
{panel}
h3. Suggestion

Allow tickets to be created and just ignore the attachments in the message.

h3. Problem Definition

In the [documentation|https://support.atlassian.com/jira-service-management-cloud/docs/link-confluence-spaces-to-your-service-project/] only mention about
{quote} * Make sure you or the Confluence group you belong to have the *View* permission for that space. If you're a Confluence admin, you can check this by navigating to your Confluence space and selecting *Space settings > Permissions.*

 * To create a new space, you need the global *Confluence administrator* and *Create space* permissions in Confluence. To manage these permissions, go to your Confluence global permissions.{quote}
Insert additional information:-
{panel}
"Service Desk Agent" permission is needed to Author or link confluence space to the service desk project. Without "Service Desk Agent" permission, the administrator will not create or link space to the service desk project.
{panel}
h3. Why this is important

The information is not complete. If the administrator group does not have a Service Desk Agent role they will not able to link or create confluence space from the service project.

Currently executing the [GET issue API|https://developer.atlassian.com/cloud/jira/platform/rest/v3/api-group-issues/#api-rest-api-3-issue-issueidorkey-get] if there's a value for "Affected Service" it'll return the following information:

{code}
"customfield_10030":[{"id":"ari:cloud:graph::service/xxxxxx-abce-xxxx-1234-xxx/1234abcd-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-12ewed281xxx4"}]
{code}

However, it's desired to know the Service Name and Tier.
